<subSubSection pageId="65" pageNumber="66" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="65.[151,1437,1374,2011]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1374,1399]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Easily distinguished from most known congeners by pale coloration, cylindrical abdomen, and relatively small male palps and epigynum. From most similar congener (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2015" box="[1033,1184,1410,1435]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Mesabolivar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kathrinae">
<emphasis box="[1033,1184,1410,1435]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">M. kathrinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) by wider procursus (compare 
<figureCitation box="[266,471,1446,1471]" captionStart="FIGURES 271–279" captionStartId="68.[151,264,1671,1693]" captionTargetBox="[159,1431,189,1642]" captionTargetId="figure@68.[151,1436,189,1663]" captionTargetPageId="68" captionText="FIGURES 271–279. Left procursi, retrolateral views. 271. Mesabolivar azureus (Badcock, 1932) (ZFMK Ar 19087). 272. M. pallens sp. n. (ZFMK Ar 19093). 273. M. kathrinae Huber, 2015 (ZFMK Ar 12621). 274–279. M. brasiliensis (Moenkhaus, 1898), males from Cantareira (274, ZFMK Ar 19106), Ubatuba (275, ZFMK Ar 19105), Paraty (276–277, ZFMK Ar 19109, 19116), Rio das Pedras (278, ZFMK Ar 19113), and Guapiaçú (279, ZFMK Ar 19110). Arrows point at present/absent dorsal widening possibly indicating presenceof two species.Scale line:0.2 (all at same scale)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202587/files/figure.png" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Figs 272 and 273</figureCitation>
), presence of proximal processes on male chelicerae (
<figureCitation box="[1095,1196,1446,1471]" captionStart="FIGURES266–270" captionStartId="66.[151,264,1944,1966]" captionTargetBox="[154,1433,469,1907]" captionTargetId="figure@66.[151,1436,469,1922]" captionTargetPageId="66" captionText="FIGURES266–270. Mesabolivar pallens sp. n. (ZFMK Ar19093). 266–267.Left male palp, prolateral and retrolateral views. 268. Male chelicerae, frontal view. 269. Epigynum, ventral view. 270. Cleared female genitalia, dorsal view. Scale lines: 0.3 (266–268), 0.2 (269–270)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202585/files/figure.png" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Fig. 268</figureCitation>
), and by presence of median pocket on epigynum (
<figureCitation box="[493,597,1482,1507]" captionStart="FIGURES266–270" captionStartId="66.[151,264,1944,1966]" captionTargetBox="[154,1433,469,1907]" captionTargetId="figure@66.[151,1436,469,1922]" captionTargetPageId="66" captionText="FIGURES266–270. Mesabolivar pallens sp. n. (ZFMK Ar19093). 266–267.Left male palp, prolateral and retrolateral views. 268. Male chelicerae, frontal view. 269. Epigynum, ventral view. 270. Cleared female genitalia, dorsal view. Scale lines: 0.3 (266–268), 0.2 (269–270)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202585/files/figure.png" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Figs 269</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[610,656,1483,1507]" captionStart="FIGURES 292–305" captionStartId="74.[151,264,1787,1809]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1765]" captionTargetId="figure@74.[151,1436,193,1765]" captionTargetPageId="74" captionText="FIGURES 292–305. Female epigyna in ventral views and cleared female genitalia in dorsal views, Mesabolivar kathrinae group and M. cyaneotaeniatus group. 292–293. M. azureus (Badcock, 1932) (ZFMK Ar 19087). 294–295. M. pallens sp. n. (ZFMK Ar 19093). 296. M. kathrinae Huber, 2015 (ZFMK Ar 12621). 297. M. sp., undescribed species (ZFMK Ar 19104), from Paraná, Fazenda Experimental Gralha Azul.298–299. M.brasiliensis (Moenkhaus, 1898), from Ubatuba (298, ZFMK Ar 19105) and Guapiaçú (299, ZFMK Ar 19110). 300–303.M.cyaneotaeniatus (Keyserling, 1891) (‘true’) from St.Hilaire/Lange (300, ZFMK Ar 19134) and Vargem Alta (301, ZFMK Ar 19136), and possible heterospecific specimens from Guapiaçú (302, ZFMK Ar 19120) and Pau Brasil (303, ZFMK Ar 19141). 304–305. M. kaingang sp. n. (ZFMK Ar 19142). Arrows point at present (300)/absent (302) dark ridges." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202593/files/figure.png" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">294</figureCitation>
). Females are externally barely distinguishable from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Moenkhaus" baseAuthorityYear="1898" box="[1267,1436,1482,1507]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Mesabolivar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brasiliensis">
<emphasis box="[1267,1436,1482,1507]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">M. brasiliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Badcock" baseAuthorityYear="1932" box="[198,322,1519,1542]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Mesabolivar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="azureus">
<emphasis box="[198,322,1519,1542]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">M. azureus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; males of these two species have very different procursi (compare 
<figureCitation box="[1072,1342,1518,1543]" captionStart="FIGURES 271–279" captionStartId="68.[151,264,1671,1693]" captionTargetBox="[159,1431,189,1642]" captionTargetId="figure@68.[151,1436,189,1663]" captionTargetPageId="68" captionText="FIGURES 271–279. Left procursi, retrolateral views. 271. Mesabolivar azureus (Badcock, 1932) (ZFMK Ar 19087). 272. M. pallens sp. n. (ZFMK Ar 19093). 273. M. kathrinae Huber, 2015 (ZFMK Ar 12621). 274–279. M. brasiliensis (Moenkhaus, 1898), males from Cantareira (274, ZFMK Ar 19106), Ubatuba (275, ZFMK Ar 19105), Paraty (276–277, ZFMK Ar 19109, 19116), Rio das Pedras (278, ZFMK Ar 19113), and Guapiaçú (279, ZFMK Ar 19110). Arrows point at present/absent dorsal widening possibly indicating presenceof two species.Scale line:0.2 (all at same scale)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202587/files/figure.png" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Figs 271, 272, 274–279</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="65" pageNumber="66" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="65.[151,1437,1374,2011]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1554,1579]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name refers to the pale greenish coloration of this species (Latin 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2018" box="[1264,1344,1554,1579]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Mesabolivar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallens">
<emphasis box="[1264,1344,1554,1579]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">pallens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
= pale, greenish); adjective.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
